-- Exxon Sells 2012 Fuel Oil to Trafigura, Dow Jones Says
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2011-12-23T10:45:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/exxon-sells-2012-fuel-oil-to-trafigura-total-dow-jones-says.html
(Corrects location of spokeswoman in story published Dec.
22.)  Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  sold  fuel oil  for
2012 by tender to Trafigura Beheer BV and Total SA, Dow Jones
reported, citing an unidentified trader.  Exxon sold as many as 12 cargoes through the year, or as
much as 60,000 metric tons a month, to Trafigura from its Fawley
refinery in the U.K., the newswire said today. Emma Heywood, an
Exxon spokeswoman based at Leatherhead in Surrey,  England ,
couldnâ€™t immediately comment on the tender when contacted by
Bloomberg News.  The company also sold as much as 1.2 million tons of the
low sulfur grade to Total from its Slagen facility in Norway,
the newswire reported yesterday. Erik Hauge, an Exxon spokesman
based in Oslo, confirmed by phone yesterday a tender had been
awarded, without giving details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
